# Next.js Conventions

## App Router
- All pages live in `src/app/`
- Use `page.tsx` for route pages, `layout.tsx` for layouts
- NEVER create a `pages/` directory

## Component patterns
- Default to Server Components (no `'use client'`)
- Add `'use client'` ONLY when you need: hooks, event handlers, browser APIs
- Keep client components small and leaf-level

## Data fetching
```typescript
// ✅ Correct — TanStack Query in client component
const { data } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['scenarios'],
  queryFn: fetchScenarios,
});

// ❌ Wrong — never do this
const [data, setData] = useState(null);
useEffect(() => { fetch('/api/...').then(...) }, []);
```

## Forms
```typescript
// ✅ Correct — React Hook Form + Zod
const { register, handleSubmit } = useForm<FormValues>({
  resolver: zodResolver(schema),
});

// ❌ Wrong — never uncontrolled or manual state forms
const [value, setValue] = useState('');
```

## Styling
- ALWAYS use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- ALWAYS use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes
- NEVER use inline styles or CSS modules

## shadcn/ui
- Import from `@/components/ui/<component>`
- NEVER use raw HTML form elements — always shadcn equivalents
- Use `Button`, `Input`, `Select`, `Card`, `Badge`, `Label`

## API calls
- All API functions live in `src/lib/api.ts`
- Use typed interfaces for all API responses
- Handle errors in mutation `onError` callbacks
